title: Orthoptists
descr: Diagnose and treat visual system disorders such as binocular vision and eye movement impairments.
experience: Extensive skill, knowledge, and experience are needed for these occupations. Many require more than five years of experience. For example, surgeons must complete four years of college and an additional five to seven years of specialized medical training to be able to do their job.
education: Most of these occupations require graduate school. For example, they may require a master's degree, and some require a Ph.D., M.D., or J.D. (law degree).
job_training: Employees may need some on-the-job training, but most of these occupations assume that the person will already have the required skills, knowledge, work-related experience, and/or training.
example: These occupations often involve coordinating, training, supervising, or managing the activities of others to accomplish goals. Very advanced communication and organizational skills are required. Examples include pharmacists, lawyers, astronomers, biologists, clergy, physician assistants, and veterinarians.

work_tasks.descr: Examine patients with problems related to ocular motility, binocular vision, amblyopia, or strabismus.

work_tasks.task: Evaluate, diagnose, or treat disorders of the visual system with an emphasis on binocular vision or abnormal eye movements.
work_tasks.descr: Evaluate, diagnose, or treat disorders of the visual system with an emphasis on binocular vision or abnormal eye movements.

work_tasks.task: Perform diagnostic tests or measurements, such as motor testing, visual acuity testing, lensometry, retinoscopy, and color vision testing.
work_tasks.descr: Perform diagnostic tests or measurements, such as motor testing, visual acuity testing, lensometry, retinoscopy, and color vision testing.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Provide nonsurgical interventions, including corrective lenses, patches, drops, fusion exercises, or stereograms, to treat conditions such as strabismus, heterophoria, and convergence insufficiency.
work_tasks.descr: Provide nonsurgical interventions, including corrective lenses, patches, drops, fusion exercises, or stereograms, to treat conditions such as strabismus, heterophoria, and convergence insufficiency.

work_tasks.task: Interpret clinical or diagnostic test results.
work_tasks.descr: Interpret clinical or diagnostic test results.

work_tasks.task: Prepare diagnostic or treatment reports for other medical practitioners or therapists.
work_tasks.descr: Prepare diagnostic or treatment reports for other medical practitioners or therapists.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Develop or use special test and communication techniques to facilitate diagnosis and treatment of children or disabled patients.
work_tasks.descr: Develop or use special test and communication techniques to facilitate diagnosis and treatment of children or disabled patients.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Provide training related to clinical methods or orthoptics to students, resident physicians, or other health professionals.
work_tasks.descr: Provide training related to clinical methods or orthoptics to students, resident physicians, or other health professionals.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Refer patients to ophthalmic surgeons or other physicians.
work_tasks.descr: Refer patients to ophthalmic surgeons or other physicians.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Develop nonsurgical treatment plans for patients with conditions such as strabismus, nystagmus, and other visual disorders.
work_tasks.descr: Develop nonsurgical treatment plans for patients with conditions such as strabismus, nystagmus, and other visual disorders.

work_tasks.title: Orthoptists
work_tasks.task: Assist ophthalmologists in diagnostic ophthalmic procedures, such as ultrasonography, fundus photography, and tonometry.
work_tasks.descr: Assist ophthalmologists in diagnostic ophthalmic procedures, such as ultrasonography, fundus photography, and tonometry.

work_tasks.task: Collaborate with ophthalmologists, optometrists, or other specialists in the diagnosis, treatment, or management of conditions such as glaucoma, cataracts, and retinal diseases.
work_tasks.descr: Collaborate with ophthalmologists, optometrists, or other specialists in the diagnosis, treatment, or management of conditions such as glaucoma, cataracts, and retinal diseases.
